lead_paragraph: Flyhalf Richie Mo'unga kicked two late penalties as the Canterbury Crusaders wore down a stubborn Auckland Blues side to move to the top of the Super Rugby standings with a 26-21 victory on Saturday.

headline.print_headline: Mo'unga Kicks Crusaders to Hard-Earned Win Over Blues
headline.main: Mo'unga Kicks Crusaders to Hard-Earned Win Over Blues
